                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Entry in the White House Map Room Log <gloss
                            target="#t_Notebook1">Notebook</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1943-09-02T23:30:00-04:00">September 2, 1943, 11:30 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>… President and <gloss target="#t_PM1">P.M.</gloss> in at 2330. Discussed coming
                    meeting of US.–British &amp; Russia as to place for it to be held. Talked
                    generally and left at 2350.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Graham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
